.Dd December 12, 2004
.Dt SA_STACKS 2
.Os
.Sh NAME
.Nm sa_stacks
.Nd register scheduler activation upcall stacks
.\" ------------------------------------------------------------
.Sh LIBRARY
.Lb libc
.\" ------------------------------------------------------------
.Sh SYNOPSIS
.In sa.h
.Ft int
.Fn sa_stacks \
    "int num" \
    "stack_t *stacks"
.\" ------------------------------------------------------------
.Sh DESCRIPTION
.Fn sa_stacks
is used to register scheduler activation upcall stacks.
.Fa stacks
is an array of
.Fa num
of
.Vt stack_t .
.Pp
An upcall handler should be registered by
.Fn sa_register
beforehand.
.\" ------------------------------------------------------------
.Sh RETURN VALUES
On success,
.Fn sa_stacks
returns the number of stacks registered.
Otherwise, a value of \-1 is returned and
.Va errno
is set to indicate the error.
.\" ------------------------------------------------------------
.Sh SEE ALSO
.Xr sa_register 2 ,
.Xr pthread 3
